cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "LIUS Cookbook: Official How-We-Use Walkthroughs for the Open-Source Daoism LLM"
message: "If you use this software or these notebooks, please cite as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Liu
    given-names: Chi-Ying
    affiliation: "Dingren Daoxue Lab"
    email: chiyingliu@gmail.com
  - name: "Dingren Daoxue Lab"
repository-code: "https://github.com/lius-cc/lius-cookbook"
url: "https://lius.cc/llm"
abstract: >-
  A set of Jupyter notebooks that demonstrate how to use the Daoism-Qwen3.5-9B
  model, the daoism-knowledge-rag dataset (95,919 nodes), and the public RAG API
  at lius.cc/api/llm-rag. Each notebook mirrors a live demo at lius.cc/llm/demos
  and is designed to be the minimum reproducible artifact for researchers who
  want to build their own Daoist-knowledge LLM applications.
keywords:
  - Daoism
  - Taoism
  - LLM
  - RAG
  - Qwen
  - religious-studies
  - chinese-philosophy
license: CC0-1.0
